No wires  are there for the voltage regulator and I'm not sure
what and how to  install it.  Any help would be greatly  appreciated.




hey Mike this is fairly eaSY .   Most split buses had the voltage  reg 
mounted on the passenger side behind the air cleaner . get a bosch reg. #30  019E is 
the new type , I think 30 019 is the old either will work.  make  t\2 lead 
wires fron your gen. matching up to thr numbers on the reg  D+ to  D+  Df to Df  
 .  now on the Sc there should ber 2  wires  a big red wire and a small 
blue/green wire these go to the B+ with  the big red wire and the smaller wire goes 
to the 61 terminal  You can run  a ground wire from the gen body to the D- 
terminal on the reg   that  all there is to it  later  mark d



